Factors

Order of levels can be

  • Arbitrary

  • Principled: ordinal or ordered by the count

Relevel by hand()

labels <- c("Jan", "Mar", "Apr", "June", "Dec")
x1 <- c("Dec", "Apr", "Jan", "Mar", "June")

x1 <- enframe(x1) %>% 
  mutate(value = fct_relevel(as_factor(value), labels))

levels(x1$value)
## [1] "Jan"  "Mar"  "Apr"  "June" "Dec"
x1 <- tibble(
  month = rep(c("Dec", "Apr", "Jan", "June", "Mar"), times = 4),
  count = rnorm(20, mean = 50, sd = 20))

levels(x1$month)
## NULL
x1 %>% 
ggplot(aes(month, count, fill = month)) +
  geom_boxplot()

x1 %>% 
  mutate(month = fct_relevel(month, labels)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(month, count, fill = month)) +
  geom_boxplot()

We can also pull first one cathegory to the front

x1 %>% 
  mutate(month = fct_reorder(month, count)) %>%
  mutate(month = fct_relevel(month, c("Dec", "Mar"))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(month, count, fill = month)) +
  geom_boxplot()

Or to the back

x1 %>% 
  mutate(month = fct_reorder(month, count)) %>%
  mutate(month = fct_relevel(month, "Dec", after = Inf)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(month, count, fill = month)) +
  geom_boxplot()

Reorder by frequency (and reverse)

x1 %>% 
  mutate(month = fct_reorder(month, count)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(month, count, fill = month)) +
  geom_boxplot()

x1 %>% 
  mutate(month = fct_rev(fct_reorder(month, count))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(month, count, fill = month)) +
  geom_boxplot()

Empty categories

Usually they are dropped if the cathegory doesnt have any values, so we need to make it explicit

forcats::gss_cat %>% 
  ggplot(aes(race)) +
  geom_bar()

forcats::gss_cat %>% 
  ggplot(aes(race)) +
  geom_bar() +
  scale_x_discrete(drop = FALSE)

  mutate(count_inc = n()) %>%

Reorder2

Reorders the factor by the y values associated with the largest x values.

age_marital <- df %>%
  filter(!is.na(age)) %>%
  count(age, marital) %>%
  group_by(age) %>%
  mutate(prop = n / sum(n))

age_marital %>% 
  ggplot(aes(age, prop, color = marital)) +
  geom_line(size = 1)

age_marital %>% 
  ggplot(aes(age, prop, color = fct_reorder2(marital, age, prop))) +
  geom_line(size = 1)

x1 %>%
  mutate(y = round(rnorm(20, mean = 0, sd = 5), 0)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y, count, color = fct_reorder2(month, y, count))) +
  geom_line(size = 1)

In frequence: fct_infreq()

df %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(rincome))) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))

df %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fct_rev(fct_infreq(rincome)))) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))

Recode

Allows to change the value of each level, factors dont not work with case_when.

It leaves all unmentioned factors as they are.

df %>% 
  count(partyid) %>% 
  head() %>% mytable()
partyid n
No answer 154
Dont know 1
Other party 393
Strong republican 2314
Not str republican 3032
Ind,near rep 1791 
df %>%
  mutate(partyid = case_when(
    partyid == "No answer" ~ "NoA",
    TRUE ~ partyid)) %>% 
  count(partyid)
## Error: must be a character vector, not a `factor` object
df %>%
  mutate(partyid = case_when(
    partyid == "No answer" ~ "NoA",
    TRUE ~ "Others")) %>% 
  count(partyid)
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   partyid     n
##   <chr>   <int>
## 1 NoA       154
## 2 Others  21329
df %>%
  mutate(partyid = fct_recode(partyid,
    "NoA" = "No answer")) %>% 
  count(partyid) %>% 
  head() %>% mytable
partyid n
NoA 154
Dont know 1
Other party 393
Strong republican 2314
Not str republican 3032
Ind,near rep 1791

Exercises

How have the proportions of people identifying as Democrat, Republican, and Independent changed over time?

df %>% 
  count(partyid)
## # A tibble: 10 x 2
##    partyid                n
##    <fct>              <int>
##  1 No answer            154
##  2 Don't know             1
##  3 Other party          393
##  4 Strong republican   2314
##  5 Not str republican  3032
##  6 Ind,near rep        1791
##  7 Independent         4119
##  8 Ind,near dem        2499
##  9 Not str democrat    3690
## 10 Strong democrat     3490
df_clean <- df %>% 
  select(year, partyid) %>% 
  mutate(
    partyid = fct_collapse(partyid,
                         republican = c("Strong republican",
                                          "Not str republican"),
                         independent = c("Ind,near rep",
                                            "Independent",
                                           "Ind,near dem"),
                         democrat = c("Not str democrat",
                                        "Strong democrat"),
                         other = c("No answer",
                                     "Don't know",
                                     "Other party"))) %>% 
  count(year, partyid)

df_clean %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  mutate(total = sum(n),
         prop = n/total) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  ggplot(aes(year, prop, color = partyid)) + 
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  geom_point(aes(shape = partyid, size = 2), show.legend = FALSE)
